Text: BackstageHeroes  Many years ago I worked with Lakmé Salon but had to move out due to personal reasons I couldnt stay away for too long  within two years I was back and have been here for five years now Ive learnt so much here theres no way I would have learnt this much and grown as a professional at any other salon company Lakmé Salon also offers job security which helps us be the best versions of ourselves and better our skills every year After becoming a Backstage Hero for which my colleagues managers and trainers encouraged me to apply my next goal is to become a Hair Trainer Ive learnt so much here and I enjoy teaching so now I want to pass this on to other aspiring stylists So far the company has been extremely supportive hence I have no doubt that I will achieve this goal in the next few years   Sadurla Chandrashekar Senior Hairstylist Lakmé Salon Hyderabad  LakmeSalon SaferThanHome Inspiring BehindTheScenes SalonExperts LakmeFashionWeek SkinExperts ExpertCare BridalMakeup RevampYourLook HappyHair HappyTresses SkinExpert SuccessStories PersonalGrowth ProfessionalGrowth SuccessMilestones SuccessStory BeautifyTheFuture

Text: BackstageHeroes  I joined Lakmé Salon in  as an Assistant Salon Manager but only really learnt about and got motivated to work in the business in  Within the next two years I was promoted to Salon Manager and today Im an Area Business Executive on my way to become an Area Business Manager The most valuable lesson Lakmé Salon taught was to break down goals and tasks to make them more achievable and to celebrate even the smallest of wins Ive been able to apply this to my personal life as well along with the communications training Ive received over the years When I joined I didnt know much about the salon industry and my spoken English wasnt fluent either But instead of highlighting my weaknesses this company took my strengths and built on them My next goal is to become a Zonal Business Manager and everyone who knows me knows that I plan to retire at Lakmé Salon   Sumaiya Ali Area Business Executive Lakmé Salon Bangalore  LakmeSalon SaferThanHome Inspiring BehindTheScenes SalonExperts LakmeFashionWeek SkinExperts ExpertCare BridalMakeup RevampYourLook HappyHair HappyTresses SkinExpert SuccessStories PersonalGrowth ProfessionalGrowth SuccessMilestones SuccessStory BeautifyTheFuture

Text: BackstageHeroes  I hail from Kanpur UP where the brand name of Lakmé Salon is a big deal When I decided I wanted to get into the beauty field I knew that doing my course at Lakmé Academy Powered by Aptech LAPA would be the best option for my career I was lucky enough to learn it all  skin hair and makeup but I soon realised that I wanted to specialise in skin therapy Though my goal has always been to someday become a trainer with Lakmé Salon my managers and trainers encouraged me to first work on the floor to gain knowledge and experience and Im so glad they did Not only am I better skilled now but my confidence has also vastly increased since I first joined Lakmé Salon in  In  I even became a Dermalogicacertified skin therapist and have so far participated in two ProSkin Master competitions reaching the final rounds both times I want to work hard and further hone my skills over the next year or two and to become a trainer and with Lakmé Salons support Im sure that will happen   Shikha Pathak Skin Therapist Lakmé Salon Delhi  LakmeSalon SaferThanHome Inspiring BehindTheScenes SalonExperts LakmeFashionWeek SkinExperts ExpertCare BridalMakeup RevampYourLook HappyHair HappyTresses SkinExpert SuccessStories PersonalGrowth ProfessionalGrowth SuccessMilestones SuccessStory BeautifyTheFuture

Text: BackstageHeroes  In the  years Ive been at Lakmé Salon Ive grown from being a trainee to a Backstage Hero which is a big deal for me Not only have I become a better professional at Lakmé Salon but the soft skills trainings Ive received over the years has also helped develop my personality outside of work The highlight of my career of course has been working backstage at Lakmé Fashion Week multiple times I think those were some of the best days of my life I started by assisting the trainers and today I have assistants when working backstage The energy there is amazing You get a great deal of exposure and also get to learn so much things you may not learn in salon My journey with Lakmé Salon has been full of learnings My next goal is to become a Hair Trainer which Im confident will happen in the next couple of years   Mayuri Pawar Senior Hairstylist  Backstage Hero Lakmé Salon Mumbai  LakmeSalon SaferThanHome Inspiring BehindTheScenes SalonExperts LakmeFashionWeek SkinExperts ExpertCare BridalMakeup RevampYourLook HappyHair HappyTresses SkinExpert SuccessStories PersonalGrowth ProfessionalGrowth SuccessMilestones SuccessStory BeautifyTheFuture

Text: Тонирующие маскибальзамышампуни   Помогут сохранить цвет после окрашивания  Нейтрализуют нежелательные оттенки  Легко применять в домашних условиях   Сушат волосы не рекомендуется часто использовать  Не заменяют полноценное тонирование волос Так как работаю лишь на поверхности волоса не наполняя его  При неправильном применении можно получить нежелательные оттенки  Многиено не все средства быстро смываются с волос изза чего им начинают чаще пользоваться а в итоге пересушивают длину    А вы пользуетесь тонирующими средствами в домашних условиях    Если у вас есть тонирующие средства и есть сомнения в правильности использования вы всегда можете написать мне в директ и я вам подскажу    На фото шампунь для поддержания рыжих оттенков Когда я была рыженькой я очень его любила за мягкую работу и насыщенность которую он придавал окрашиванию   колористекб парикмахерекб уходдляволос уходдляволосекб тонированиеволосекб тонирующиемаскидляволос тонирующийшампунь тонированиеблондаекб тонированиеволос волосыекбокрашиваниеволосекб сложныеокрашиванияекб фиолетовыйшампунь тонирующаямаска lakme lakmeshampoo lakmecosmetics

Text: Atelier Opening Outhouse at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  Outhouses collection OH Dopamine was all about celebrating a strong sense of self expression in an unapologetic way From an idyllic escape into the world of fantasies to an eclectic sense of being ones unapologetic self the designers rediscovered the joys in the little memories from their past by diving into the exuberant spirit of the s Encapsulating the very essence of the YK era the line featured colourful beads resin seed beads raffia and even enamel with each creation having its own individualistic charm Echoing the strong voice of the collection the pieces are an interplay as a motley of silver plating combined with matte silver along with crystals and rhinestones Their exceptional craftsmanship shone through their exquisite handbags shining bright with metallic undertones  outhousejewellery lakmesalon lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: Presenting Diksha Khanna at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  dikshakhannas collection titled Julley or Hello in Ladakhi was inspired by the barren landscape of Ladakh The transseasonal  fluid line entails traditional costumes that were interpreted in insightful shapes and dexterous detailing making ensembles mostly androgynous She went back to the roots to explore ecoprinting a form of natural dyeing on textiles to extract the natural beauty of plants  foliage  lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakmeFashionWeek LakmeFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW yearsofSFD SustainableFashionDay ChangeIsGood

tencel_luxe presents JJV BY JJ Valayas collection RumeliThe Summer Story at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week was engineered with a sensitivity towards sustainability This year as the luxury occasion wear brand celebrates its th year in fashion it takes a step further by launching its allnew bridgetoluxury brand JJV The new brand debuted with an ecoconscious collection made from TENCEL LUXE filament yarn which is a sustainable ecofriendly and vegan alternative to silk Derived from renewable wood sources in a closed loop lyocell process TENCEL LUXE filament yarn is set to define the landscape of luxury fashion with its silky smoothness liquidlike drape color vibrancy and yarn strength JJV is an occasion wear brand that revolves around the spirit of travel  with this exquisite line it embraces the need where one can still maintain a unique sense of personal style without the use of any heavy embroideries   mrunalthakur jjvalaya tencel_luxe lakmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide   ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW TencelLuxeatFDCIxLFW Tencelluxe Vegan Vegansilk sustainablesilk consciousluxury

Extracting natural colours from soil water and air   Indian fashion designer ka_sha_india collaborated with our innovator kbcolssciences  a biotech studio that produces sustainable natural colours from living microorganisms  The collection designed and created for fdciofficial x lakmefashionwk  in India is called Manthan and celebrates water and its quality of acting plurally ever changing yet calm shapeless yet creating shape and an important factor in both life and death The pieces exhibited are embellished with handembroidered fish and reference marine life with a natural colour palette using handdyed fabrics from the innovator  Curious to see it up close The creations are part of our current exhibition Fashion Week A New Era at the Fashion for Good Museum  head to the link in our bio to book tickets   fashioninnovation sustainability sustainablemuseum fashionmuseum fashionweek futureoffashion airpollution

Text: Presenting Vaishali S Couture at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  Vaishali S Coutures collection Fil Rouge followed through the reassessment of key pillars which also define the arc of the designers creative journey The collection composed of textures and stateoftheart silhouettes mostly speaking through layers and mixes of drapes and constructions inspired from different weaves of India Subtle hues all the way from black to colors convey festivity but also tranquility and balance Sustainability being the strong focus and with the aim of making it transparent also to the customers the designer through her pieces has traced all processes through Blockchain in order to make it clear and certain  shalinipassi vaishalisstudio lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW yearsofSFD SustainableFashionDay ChangeIsGood

Text: Siddartha Tytler at FDCI x Lakmé Fashion Week  Siddartha Tytlers collection took inspiration from the art of Sometsuke Sometsuke is a Japanese term referring to the technique of decorating ceramics with brushpainted designs in underglaze cobalt blue on a white ground Transparent glaze is applied on top of this painted bisque before firing producing a vivid shade of blue that is known in China as qinghua literally blue flower  It comprised of applique crystal splashes heavy sequin sheeting ruffles and digital prints commissioned by an artist It had something for everybody from swimwear to heavily embroidered couture lehengas  siddartha_tytler lakmeindia lakmesalon nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: Presenting NEXA presents Tarun Tahiliani Luxury Pret at FDCI x Lakme Fashion Week  nexaexperience presents taruntahiliani Luxury Pret at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week was a beautiful expression of modern India and is global at the same time It shows the amalgamation of modern and traditional silhouettes as well as drapes with technology and aerodynamics Here structured draping marries tech There were prints in the collection which have been distorted and recreated in the most beautiful textiles Innovative at its core the textiles in this collection have been woven with a Zari thread and Resham to create metallic textured sheen and look like molten metals This collection iwas a new take on the future generation that is confident experimental has fashion in its roots and values avantgarde design  kritisanon nexaexperience lakmeindia tresemmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW NEXAatLFW NEXALifestyle CreateInspire Nexaexperience NEXAInnovativeExperiences nexalifestyle

Text: Presenting RElan X Satya Paul by Rajesh Pratap Singh at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  In collaboration with RElan Satya Paul by Rajesh Pratap Singh showcased New Order  a collection that spells Evening with a capital E  reminds us of the power of art The smart  sustainable fabrics provided by RElan gives flight to their lines flow Music fashion and the right to creative expression belong in the streets and public institutions Breaking free with all due respect the collection urges us to be reminded that we have the right to dance in the office Inspiration is taken from the work of Klimt Muccha and Toulouse Lautrec at the time when art nouveau emerged as resistance and they demanded through their work a return to nature  relanofficial rajeshpratapsinghworks satyapaulindia lakmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLFW FDCIxLakmeFashionWeek LakmeFashionWeek DaysofFashion LFW CircularDesignChallenge yearsofSFD SustainableFashionDay FabricOfTheFuture RElanatFDCIxLFW MakeFashionGood

Text: Presenting Punit Balana at FDCI x Lakmé Fashion Week  Designer Punit Balanas new collection Lakshmi took inspiration from the journey of a young urbane cosmopolitan girl Lakshmi who is well travelled has explored the world yet is very rooted The collection is an artistic expression which beautifully blends culture and art form deeply rooted in Rajasthan The ensembles are replete with bold motifs in Rajasthani natural vegetable dye using Kalamkari  ajrak technique on luscious chanderi silk rendering a surrealistic vision Explorative  layered metallic embroidery on prints  solid tones using coins thread  mirror breathes magic into diaphanous palates of neutrals tones of henna and earthy hues A sense of fluidity and ease with movement was the core of Balanas new collection Each and every ensemble has been designed to be moved danced and celebrated in  janhvikapoor punitbalanaofficial lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: Rani Padmini also known as Padmavati was the queen of Mewar married to Maharawal Ratan Singh ji She was a woman of unprecedented beauty She was not only beautiful but also fierce Rani Padmini was well trained in war strategies and battlefield This made her adept at the art of swordmanship After her husband Ratan Singh was killed in battle she walked down a secret passage within the fort that led to the Jauhar Kund Rani Padmini was the first to jump into the Jauhar Kund fearless and brave   I am so elated that lakmesalon recreated the Luminous look inspired by Rani Padmavati on me from their queentessential bridal collection The experts gave me open soft curls and for the makeup they went with a reverse eyeliner and heavy gold smokey shimmer eyes The stunning jewellery completed the look and I am so happy about how this turned out to be  Outfit  sugnamalofficial sugnamal  Jewellery orrajewellery dazzlesjewellery   lakmesalon Bridal MakeUp QueentessentialBride HappyHair happyyou weddinglook reelsinstagram reels explorepage explore padmavati

Text: Presenting Rara Avis by Sonal Verma and Shruti Sancheti at FDCI x Lakmé Fashion Week  Rara Avis by Sonal Vermas collection Hodophilic at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week was a reflection of all those thoughts that come together to make you feel alive The collection featured silhouettes that are buoyant yet easy There was a strong play of colours amongst which tonal embroidered details stood out with the use of old traditional Indian techniques The jewellery line was made of only natural stones It was an extension of the sensibility that is contemporary  sublime echoing the ethos of the brand  Shruti Sanchetis collection Alchemy was an ode to those who know that the magical thing about home is that even though it feels good to leave it feels even better to come back Using Laborious techniques from the Mughal era coupled with delicate details handcrafted by craftsmen  the collection promised pieces that carry a timeless appeal This was the personification of Slow fashion with a look that is global combined with a soul that is totally indigenous Sustainable detailoriented and a celebration of the unsurpassed legacy of craft and textiles of India sums up her exquisite line  raraavisbysonalverma _shrutisancheti lakmeindia tresemmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: Rise Worldwide x Fashion For Good present Innovation for Circularity featuring Divyam Mehta Kasha  Nitin Bal Chauhan at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week   rseworldwide  fashionforgood joined hands to catalyse collaborations between supply chain disruptors and designers to present collections that spotlight Innovations for Circular fashion   divyammehta took on a poetic spin on the Dongria Kondh tribe silhouettes that reflect a rural life culture and simple living in tune with nature The fabrics came from AltMat an enterprise that develops textiles from agricultural waste Drapes hybrid patterns hand tailoring kantha work are some of the key elements of this capsule collection   ka_sha_indias collection Manthan took its inspiration from the paradoxical nature of water that is everchanging The surfaces of the pieces represented the many layers of water both tangible and intangible with the help of handdyeing using KB cols Sciences microbial fermentation technology and nonGMO naturally occurring coloured microbes This collection was made in cotton of differing weights that are appliqued embroidered and pleated to bring to life the designers inspiration   nitinbalchauhan came up with a conceptual collection Countdown designed to raise awareness on how our collective action and nonsustainable growth is leading our planet to a point of no return at an alarming speed The collection addressed grave issues like urbanisation deforestation air pollution that resulted in increased alarming diseases It used Gravikys AirInk for printing  painting ink that is made from carbon collected from vehicles chimneys etc   lakmeindia fdciofficial   ExploreMore FDCIxLakmeFashionWeek LakmeFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW yearsofSFD SustainableFashionDay RiseAtLFW

Text: Atelier Opening Outhouse at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  Outhouses collection OH Dopamine was all about celebrating a strong sense of self expression in an unapologetic way From an idyllic escape into the world of fantasies to an eclectic sense of being ones unapologetic self the designers rediscovered the joys in the little memories from their past by diving into the exuberant spirit of the s Encapsulating the very essence of the YK era the line featured colourful beads resin seed beads raffia and even enamel with each creation having its own individualistic charm Echoing the strong voice of the collection the pieces are an interplay as a motley of silver plating combined with matte silver along with crystals and rhinestones Their exceptional craftsmanship shone through their exquisite handbags shining bright with metallic undertones  outhousejewellery lakmesalon lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: John Jacob presents Shivan and Narresh at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  Shivan and Narreshs Fresconian Series at the FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week was all about reimagining the visual splendor of Shekhawati Havelis in Rajasthan painting to life Indias opulent history and evolution through the modern lens of art and design The contemporarisation of the mural musings and their newage relevance in documenting and eternalizing the Shekhawati history and the lives of the people at that time enamors and inspires a modern canvas for the Fresconian Series  prints were used in this collection which pay an ode to the artist as well as the artisans exuding joy and creativity through poetic blends of shimmering skein luster and meticulous detailing Handtechniques such as hand knitting crochet handmachine embroidery and shuttle needlelace technique hero the intricacy of each garment  harnaazsandhu_ johnjacobseyewear lakmesalon shivanandnarresh lakmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW JohnJacobsatFDCIxLFW johnjacobseyewear jjfam

Text: Siddartha Tytler at FDCI x Lakmé Fashion Week  Siddartha Tytlers collection took inspiration from the art of Sometsuke Sometsuke is a Japanese term referring to the technique of decorating ceramics with brushpainted designs in underglaze cobalt blue on a white ground Transparent glaze is applied on top of this painted bisque before firing producing a vivid shade of blue that is known in China as qinghua literally blue flower  It comprised of applique crystal splashes heavy sequin sheeting ruffles and digital prints commissioned by an artist It had something for everybody from swimwear to heavily embroidered couture lehengas  siddartha_tytler lakmeindia nexaexperience fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW

Text: realme presents Shantnu and Nikhil at the FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  The collection nomad was a new direction a way of looking at design as a responsibility as well as a great power With this collection the designers seek to turn the art of design into a weapon a tool and a refuge and through it to imagine newer more hopeful worlds and to cast our minds into the future  This collection brought all that was happening around us through symbols textures silhouettes and motifs There were sweaters in rough knits that seem like they were made of ropeyarn suited to a breezy beachside while classic intarsia featuring large leopard spots were cut into voluminous jackets for the urban jungle There were huge bags and vintage fisher hats alluding to the constant Nomad in all of us while puffer jackets and studded harnesses coalesce comfort and couture  shantanunikhil realmeindia lakmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide  ExploreMore FDCIxLakméFashionWeek LakméFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW RealmeatFDCIxLFW realmeGTPro

Text: Bemberg Presents Payal Pratap at FDCI X Lakmé Fashion Week  Payal Pratap took a nostalgic journey with this collection aptly named JAVA With a focus on prints the designer has worked on hand painted artworks which have then been digitized The designs capture detailed elements and a threedimensional depth and texture from the ageold crafts of Batik and powerful imagery and minute detailing from the ancient craft of Chintz printing   The prints encompassed of flora and fauna bringing nature from the outside to the inside through the use of extensive flower leaf tree vines and bird motives as an ode to sustainability Bemberg in various avatars ranging from satins muslins mulmul and silk blends have been used to create a collection with fluid drapes as well as structure The line of clothing features bold prints  large floral patterns and  is clearly a return to maximalism reminiscent of the good old days   bemberg_india payalpratap lakmeindia fdciofficial rseworldwide   ExploreMore FDCIxLakmeFashionWeek LakmeFashionWeek FDCIxLFW DaysOfFashion LFW yearsofSFD SustainableFashionDay ChangeIsGood BembergatFDCIxLFW BembergIndia CraftedElegance Bemberg Cupro Asahikasei
